      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 49,
      "message": "I envision some limitations of FirstBlocksSecond coordination policy if we define policy type like this. It will only coordinate two controlloops with the same actor and recipe. What about different actors/recipes but the same target? In my opinion, FirstBlocksSecond is a more general coordination function. It can be applied to two controlloops with arbitrary actor,recipe,target ideally.",
